\begin_layout Subsection
Precautionary motives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While literature focuses much attention to market timing, a very interesting
 paper of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "davidmclean2011shareissuance"

\end_inset

 propose the precautionary motive of share issuances.
 When precautionary motive is higher over time, firms tend to issue stocks
 in good times to save cash.
 As a result, cash saving from stock issuances increases over time.
 During 1970s, firms save $0.23/$1 share issuance, but over the most recent
 decade, the ratio is 0.6/1.
 However, he propose two contrasting hypotheses in this paper for this trend:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Precautionary motive
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Market timing: firms issue when market is overvalued and share repurchase
